The paper proposes a hybridization of two popular clustering algorithms, Expectation-Maximization (EM) and K-Means, to improve clustering performance. This work falls under the category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper. However, given the focus on clustering algorithms and performance evaluation, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
